</taxonomicName>
, male and female from Açores (“… Furnas …”); E: body of lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackburn" authorityYear="1902" box="[1136,1268,1899,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wattsensis">
<emphasis box="[1136,1268,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">B. wattsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male from VIC (
<bibRefCitation author="Blackburn, T." box="[158,384,1934,1958]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="288 - 321" refId="ref104005" refString="Blackburn, T. (1902) Further notes on Australian Coleoptera, with description of new genera and species. XXXI. Transactions and Proceedings and Report of the Royal Society of South Australia, 26, 288 - 321." type="journal article" year="1902">Blackburn, 1902: 304</bibRefCitation>
: “Watts River district”); paralectotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackburn" authorityYear="1902" box="[803,935,1935,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wattsensis">
<emphasis box="[803,935,1935,1958]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">B. wattsensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, female from the same series; 
